<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--Nudists'Blood     06-19 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Nudists' Blood,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nudists ``Roll Up Sleeves'' for Blood Drive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARCOLA, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When it comes to canvassing for blood
donations, not even nudists are spared.
   While the nudists usually put their clothes on before they step
into the bloodmobile, many were wandering about the Willamettans
Nudist Camp in various stages of undress Friday. But the Lane County
Bloodmobile workers took it in stride.
   ``It's good blood,'' worker Pat Smith said. ``Their blood
pressure always seems to be low. One of the ways to keep your blood
pressure down is to be cool.''
   For the nudists, the blood drive was not unusual _ not like the
time they had a clothing drive.
   They were only glad to roll up their sleeves and help out.
   ``We might make nudists out of the nurses yet,'' said Jim Petree,
the park's host. ``We tease them every time they come out. We say,
`Come up and see more of us.'''
</TEXT>
