<DOCNO> AP890619-0051 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-19-89 0828EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r p PM-Pepper'sSeat     06-19 0294</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Pepper's Seat,0302</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pepper's Brother Critical of Niece for Announcing Candidacy</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JACKIE HALLIFAX</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The sole surviving sibling of U.S. Rep.
Claude Pepper said he wants the best qualified Democrat elected to
his late brother's seat _ and he doesn't think their niece is that
candidate.
   ``It appears she has been talked into something about which she
knows very little,'' Frank Pepper said Sunday after learning that
JoAnn Pepper had entered the race.
   Ms. Pepper, 38, joined two other Democrats running for the seat
her late uncle held for 27 years until his death at age 88 on May 30.
   Frank Pepper, a 71-year-old retired broadcaster, said he learned
of his niece's intentions from reading the newspaper and was never
consulted.
   Ms. Pepper, a federal probation officer, is the adopted daughter
of the late Joseph Pepper, brother to Frank and Claude. In his will,
Claude Pepper left her $50,000.
   ``She was very, very close to (Claude Pepper), like a daughter to
him, and she would like to continue with his work,'' said Maria
Tolon, the late congressman's Hispanic liaison in Miami.
   Claude Pepper was one of the nation's leading advocates for the
elderly and poor during a political career that began in the
Legislature in the 1930s.
   Educator Marvin Dunn and retired industrialist Bernard Anscher
already have entered the race for the Democratic nomination.
   Frank Pepper said he supported either one and hoped ``the
best-qualified Democrat will win and continue the fight for the
elderly and the unconnected to which my dear brother Claude devoted
his entire public life.''
   Announced candidates for the GOP nomination are state Sen. Ileana
Ros-Lehtinen, lawyer Jeff Allen and Carlos Perez, a businessman and
conservative activist. The primary is Aug. 1.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
