<FIRST>r a PM-Hoffa-FBI     06-19 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Hoffa-FBI,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>FBI Agent Claims to Know Who Killed Hoffa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A retiring FBI agent says he knows who killed
Jimmy Hoffa but can't say.
   ``I'm comfortable I know who did it, but it's never going to be
prosecuted because we would have to divulge informants, confidential
sources,'' Kenneth P. Walton, FBI chief in Detroit from 1985 to
1988, said in Sunday's Detroit News.
   ``There was more than one person who killed Jimmy Hoffa or was
involved in the efforts. (But) we can't force a source, for example,
to testify,'' said the 24-year agent.
   Walton declined to be specific but said some informants and
suspects are dead.
   Hoffa's son said the FBI could ease the family's pain by
dispelling some of the mystery surrounding the 1975 disappearance of
the former Teamsters boss.
   ``I think it is incumbent upon the FBI, if in fact they do know
who was involved in the slaying of my father, that they share that
information with the family,'' James Hoffa said in today's Detroit
Free Press.
