themselves, and when asked what they intended to do with the
seminarians, replied they would ``teach them something useful.''
   He said he doubted the gunmen were rebels of the Sudan People's
Liberation Army.
   The rebels took up arms in 1983 against the Moslem-dominated
Khartoum government to press for autonomy and economic development
for the predominantly Christian and animist south.
