<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--PatriotismPoll     06-19 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Patriotism Poll,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Poll: Patriotism Thriving in America</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release 6 p.m. EDT</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About three in four Americans say the country
needs more patriotism, according to a poll commissioned by Parents
magazine.
   The survey of 1,000 adults also found that 73 percent favored ``a
high level of patriotism.'' Fifty-three percent said they owned an
American flag, and 64 percent of them said they displayed it on the
last Fourth of July.
   Fifty-eight percent said cheating on one's income taxes was
unpatriotic, and a similar percentage agreed it was unpatriotic not
to vote. Sixty-three percent said it was patriotic to buy only
American products.
   The telephone interview of 1,000 people 21 and over was conducted
in late January using a random national sample. The margin of error
was 3.1 percent.
</TEXT>
