<HEAD>Border Police Arrest Man Drilling Hole in Berlin Wall</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: ADDS 1 graf of detail from witnesses.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West Berlin man was arrested by East German
border guards Monday as he drilled a hole in the Berlin Wall, police
said.
   West Berlin police said the man was arrested while using a
jackhammer on the West Berlin side of the wall to drill a hole in
the concrete barrier.
   The Berlin Wall, which divides the city, is set back several
yards from the actual border. The man was standing on East German
territory at the time of his arrest, West Berlin police said.
   Police said they had no information about the man and did not
know why he was drilling the hole.
   Witnesses said the man, in his 30s, told them he was drilling in
protest because East German authorities won't allow his mother to
travel to the West.
