   EDITOR'S NOTE _ Almost half of America's families take a vacation
every year, spending some $365 billion, and the pace is picking up.
Americans are far and away the most traveled people in the world,
trailed a distant second by the Jae Europe is still
the favorite destination abroad for most tourists, some exotic
out-of-the way places are gaining in popularity.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By JOHN BARBOUR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Newsfeatures Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   This Fourth of Julypanese. And whil, much of America won't be at home.
   Americans, more than any other nationality in the world, indulge
in a traditional and expensive compulsion to get out of town. To
scram, to leave the city, state, country. They are the world's
busiest travelers by far.
   And in the future they may be able to exit the planet, if not yet
the solar system. Two hundred have already signed up to do so.
   The average American household spends almost $4,000 a year on its
wanderlust, as much as it spends on food, twice as much as it spends
on clothing and three-fifths as much as it spends on the roof over
its head.
   Every year the American dollar travels farther. Business travel
aside, world travelers spend almost $1.3 trillionhe media giant's plans
to buy Warner
Communications Inc. in order to thwart a hostile takeover by
Paramount Communications Inc.
</TEXT>
