<HEAD>Share Prices Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices moved higher Monday as a more positive
tone in the market resulted in an upward drift.
   However, trading volume remained at recent light levels as many
players stayed on the sidelines awaiting a clearer direction for the
market this week. The next indicator will be Tuesday's British money
supply figures for May.
   Dealers said there were no substantive factors which contributed
to the higher prices, but said the combination of guardedly bullish
weekend press reports for equities, a firmer British currency and
news from the Confederation of British Industry that high interest
rates are beginning to dampen demand in the economy all helped
sentiment.
   At midday, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was
up 10.5 points, at 2,154.4, its best level for the day.
   Volume was a light 214 million shares, compared with 273.2
million shares at the same time Friday.
