<FIRST>r f PM-Atlantis-Trump     06-19 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Atlantis-Trump,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bankruptcy Judge Issues Temporary Order Against Trump's Bid For Atlantis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A federal bankruptcy judge today issued a
temporary restraining order blocking Donald Trump's $63 million bid
to buy the debt-ridden Elsinore's Atlantis Casino Hotel.
   After a brief hearing, U.S. District Court Judge Rosemary
Gambardella granted the request by creditors who hold mortgages on
three of the Atlantic City casino's parking lots.
   The creditors said they weren't given adequate notice of details
surrounding the proposed offer. They also want the judge to force
Elsinore Corp. to find a higher bidder.
   On Friday, the state Casino Control Commission ended three days
of hearings on the sale by voting unanimously to allow Trump to buy
the casino and convert it into a luxury, non-casino hotel.
   Trump's attorneys would not comment on how today's decision might
affect the proposed sale, which is slated for closing July 7.
   The casino was the first in Atlantic City to not have its license
renewal approved by state gaming officials.
   Ms. Gambardella scheduled another hearing for June 29.
</TEXT>
